The paper deals with Bayesian neural networks and their probabilistic inference using variational Bayes. This topic falls under the broad category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the application of the method to regression tasks, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV) and control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper introduces a novel method for approximating moments in neural networks, which is a technique commonly used in neuroscience (cs.NE).
